title: Rivian Eyes New Debt Deal as Expected Vehicle Deliveries Slump
content: A Rivian R1T electric vehicle (EV) pickup truck, left, and R1S electric sports utility vehicle (SUV) at the company's showroom in New York, US, on Tuesday, Jan. 2, 2024. Rivian Automotive Inc. missed expectations for quarterly electric vehicle deliveries, weighing on the manufacturer's shares even as production ramped up during the past year.
summary: jpmorgan chase & co. is leading a potential high-yield bond sale for electronic vehicle manufacturer rivian automotive inc., partly to refinance its upcoming debt, according to people familiar with the transaction.
